		<title>Cloudsmith Raises $72M to Secure the AI Software Supply Chain</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/cloudsmith-raises-72m-to-secure-the-ai-software-supply-chain/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 13:29:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200269</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Cloudsmith has raised $72 million in a Series C funding round. The investment is specifically earmarked to address the &#8220;exploding&#8221; volume of code generated by AI agents, which has fundamentally</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cloudsmith-raises-72m-to-secure-the-ai-software-supply-chain/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cloudsmith Raises $72M to Secure the AI Software Supply Chain</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://cloudsmith.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cloudsmith </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $72 million in a Series C </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/salmon-bags-100m-to-scale-digital-banking-solutions/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The investment is specifically earmarked to address the &#8220;exploding&#8221; volume of code generated by AI agents, which has fundamentally altered the landscape of software supply chain security.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by TCV and Insight Partners, with existing investors participating. This new round comes a year after its Series B, showing strong demand for cloud-native artefact management.<br />
</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rise of the &#8220;Agentic&#8221; Supply Chain</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The core of Cloudsmith&#8217;s thesis is that the era of &#8220;hand-crafted&#8221; software is rapidly ending. As AI coding agents become standard in the enterprise, the sheer volume of software artefacts (the binaries, packages, and containers that make up an application) has reached a breaking point.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200271" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200271" class="size-full wp-image-200271" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Cloudsmith.jpg" alt="Cloudsmith" width="480" height="131" /><p id="caption-attachment-200271" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Cloudsmith</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;AI agents generate so much software, so fast, that it’s nearly impossible for humans to manually review it all,&#8221; said Glenn Weinstein, CEO of Cloudsmith. &#8220;We are providing the scale and the guardrails required to govern every package. You can&#8217;t secure an AI-driven supply chain with legacy tools built for a slower, human-led world.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Traditional security tools often focus on the source code level. </span>However, Cloudsmith operates at the artefact layer, acting as a secure &#8220;single source of truth&#8221; for all third-party libraries. By sitting between the public internet and a company’s internal developers, Cloudsmith can scan, quarantine, and verify code.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/salmon-bags-100m-to-scale-digital-banking-solutions/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Salmon Bags $100M to Scale Digital Banking Solutions</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifting from Legacy to Cloud-Native</span></h2>
<p>The funding comes as Fortune 500 companies face regulatory pressure to provide a software bill of materials (SBOM). Many of organizations are finding legacy, &#8220;on-premise first&#8221; tools struggle to scale in the cloud or integrate with AI-assisted DevOps.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cloudsmith’s platform is entirely cloud-native and universal, supporting over 30 package formats. This allows it to act as a centralised &#8220;control plane&#8221; for global engineering teams, ensuring that whether code is written by a junior developer in London or an AI agent in a cloud sandbox, it follows the same security and compliance protocols.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Expansion and AI Research &amp; Development</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $72 million will be used to scale Cloudsmith&#8217;s go-to-market operations and double down on AI-specific research &amp; development. A key area of focus is the company’s newly launched Model Registry, which treats machine learning models as software artefacts. This ensures that the models themselves are subject to the same rigorous provenance and security checks as traditional code.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Morgan Gerlak, Partner at TCV, noted that the decision to lead a second consecutive round was driven by Cloudsmith’s unique position. &#8220;As AI shapes the software supply chain, we believe Cloudsmith is becoming the backbone that enterprises rely on for compliance and control at a global scale.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the &#8220;agentic&#8221; era of software development takes hold, Cloudsmith&#8217;s rapid rise suggests that the battle for cybersecurity has moved from the editor to the repository. For the modern enterprise, the question is no longer just &#8220;Who wrote this code?&#8221; But can we trust this artefact?</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cloudsmith-raises-72m-to-secure-the-ai-software-supply-chain/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cloudsmith Raises $72M to Secure the AI Software Supply Chain</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
