		<title>UNIVITY Raises €27M for Sovereign Space Connectivity</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/univity-raises-e27m-for-sovereign-space-connectivity/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:33:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200263</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>UNIVITY has brought in €27 million in Series A funding. The round was completed on 23 April 2026 and is focused on pushing forward the growth of the company&#8217;s &#8220;sovereign&#8221;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/univity-raises-e27m-for-sovereign-space-connectivity/" data-wpel-link="internal">UNIVITY Raises €27M for Sovereign Space Connectivity</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.univity.global/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">UNIVITY </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has brought in €27 million in Series A funding. The <a href="https://ventureburn.com/salmon-bags-100m-to-scale-digital-banking-solutions/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal">round</a> was completed on 23 April 2026 and is focused on pushing forward the growth of the company&#8217;s &#8220;sovereign&#8221; space infrastructure programme. This is an indigenous alternative to US-controlled behemoths such as SpaceX&#8217;s Starlink or Amazon&#8217;s Project Kuiper.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by Blast and Expansion, with a large contribution from the Deeptech 2030 fund, managed by Bpifrance on behalf of the French state for the France 2030 industrial programme. It also included investments from two private family offices. Total funding received to date, including a €31 million contract with the French space agency (CNES), has exceeded €60 million.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2022 by Charles Delfieux, UNIVITY (formerly known as Constellation Technologies &amp; Operations) is not positioning itself as a direct competitor to mobile network operators. Instead, it is building a &#8220;wholesale space infrastructure&#8221;. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While Starlink sells directly to consumers, UNIVITY’s model allows traditional telecom operators to lease space-based capacity to expand their own 5G networks. This strategy enables carriers to provide high-speed, low-latency internet to remote areas, connected vehicles, and smartphones using their own existing spectrum and branding.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The VLEO Advantage</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Central to UNIVITY’s technical edge is its use of Very Low Earth Orbit (VLEO). By operating at altitudes below 375 km—significantly closer to Earth than the ~550 km used by Starlink—UNIVITY&#8217;s satellites can deliver the following:</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200265" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200265" class="size-large wp-image-200265" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Cell-towers-1024x576.jpg" alt="Cell towers" width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-200265" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Lower Latency</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Shorter distances over which signals travel will lead to a shorter lag time in response times, which is extremely important in 5G.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Smaller Terminals</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: It enables more reduction in ground hardware, as would be needed for direct smartphone links without special antennas.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Sustainability</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Satellites in VLEO experience more atmospheric drag, ensuring that at the end of their life cycle, they naturally de-orbit and burn up within months, drastically reducing the risk of orbital debris.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/salmon-bags-100m-to-scale-digital-banking-solutions/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Salmon Bags $100M to Scale Digital Banking Solutions</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Bridging the Connectivity Gap</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One of UNIVITY’s key goals is to provide dependable connectivity in those locations where traditional infrastructure is inadequate. Remote industrial locations, rural communities, and offshore locations often have limited or fluctuating access to network connections. UNIVITY intends to utilise satellite technology to ensure coverage is delivered.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This feature works especially well in markets where construction of physical infrastructure can be costly or logistically difficult. Having sovereign space connectivity allows telecommunication companies to widen their scope of operation without any undue compromise on quality or security.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Matter of Sovereignty</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round underscores a growing urgency in Europe to maintain control over its communications infrastructure. Stéphane Lefevre-Sauli, Senior Investment Director at Bpifrance, noted that UNIVITY’s technology is &#8220;critical to enabling telecom operators to remain competitive and independent&#8221; in a market increasingly dominated by non-European players.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By partnering with French infrastructure operator TDF to host gateway stations, UNIVITY is ensuring that the data flowing through its &#8220;celestial 5G masts&#8221; remains within a framework of European regulatory and security standards.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/univity-raises-e27m-for-sovereign-space-connectivity/" data-wpel-link="internal">UNIVITY Raises €27M for Sovereign Space Connectivity</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
