					<description><![CDATA[<p>Wasabi Technologies has raised $250 million in a credit facility to scale its global infrastructure and develop specialised AI-ready storage. Bain Capital’s Private Credit Group led the credit facility and</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/wasabi-technologies-secures-250m-for-cloud-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Wasabi Technologies Secures $250M for Cloud Expansion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://wasabi.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Wasabi Technologies</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has raised $250 million in a </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/neocognition-secures-40m-seed-funding-with-intel-ceo/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">credit </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">facility to scale its global infrastructure and develop specialised AI-ready storage.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bain Capital’s Private Credit Group led the credit facility and comes at an interesting time for the Boston-headquartered unicorn as it seeks to position itself as the premier challenger to &#8216;hyperscale&#8217; players Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud and Microsoft Azure. Other highlights of the facility include U.S. Private Credit Investments (a division of BTG Pactual Global Alternatives), Neuberger Speciality Finance and Energy Impact Partners. </span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling for the AI Era</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This latest capital infusion is specifically earmarked for the build-out of Wasabi’s physical infrastructure across its 16 global storage regions. As enterprises grapple with the massive data requirements of generative AI and machine learning (ML), the demand for &#8220;always-hot&#8221; storage, data that is instantly accessible without the penalty of egress fees, has reached a fever pitch.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200243" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200243" class="size-full wp-image-200243" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Wasabi-Technologies.jpg" alt="Wasabi Technologies" width="480" height="113" /><p id="caption-attachment-200243" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Wasabi Technologies</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We are investing in our infrastructure to meet a growing global demand for data, particularly as AI and modern applications require storage that is both scalable and accessible,&#8221; said Michael Bayer, chief financial officer of Wasabi Technologies. &#8220;Even in a more selective lending market, our disciplined business model continues to attract top-tier financial support.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The move follows the recent launch of Wasabi Fire, a new NVMe-based storage class designed for compute-intensive AI training and real-time inference. Unlike traditional cloud providers that often charge &#8220;egress fees&#8221; to move data out of their ecosystem, Wasabi’s model relies on a flat, predictable pricing structure that is roughly 80% cheaper than the hyperscalers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/neocognition-secures-40m-seed-funding-with-intel-ceo/?amp=1" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">NeoCognition Secures $40M Seed Funding With Intel CEO</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A String of Strategic Wins</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $250 million credit facility is the latest in a series of high-profile manoeuvres for the company in 2026. Earlier this year, Wasabi closed a $70 million equity round led by L2 Point Management, which included participation from Pure Storage. That round valued the company at $1.8B.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More recently, Wasabi completed the purchase of Lyve Cloud from Seagate Technology, which dramatically increased the customer base and scale of operations. With over three exabytes of data and an esteemed client list that includes the Red Sox and Liverpool Football Club, Wasabi is now an established player in the cloud storage industry, valued at $100 billion, rather than a startup target.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Disrupting the Hyperscale Status Quo</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing highlights a growing trend in the tech sector: the &#8220;unbundling&#8221; of the cloud. While AWS and Azure offer a vast suite of services from databases to virtual machines, Wasabi’s &#8220;pure-play&#8221; focus on storage allows it to optimise performance and cost in ways the giants cannot.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to the 2026 Wasabi Global Cloud Storage Index, nearly 50% of the average organisation&#8217;s cloud storage bill is currently tied to hidden fees rather than actual capacity. By eliminating these fees, Wasabi has become a darling for IT directors who are struggling to keep AI project budgets under control.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Wasabi’s growth trajectory and strong fundamentals reflect a critical need in the market,&#8221; noted Andrea Lucido, Director at Bain Capital. &#8220;Data is becoming the lifeblood of how enterprises make decisions. Providing a secure, cost-effective foundation for that data is essential.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As Wasabi prepares for its next phase, the company remains focused on its &#8220;zero-fee&#8221; mission, banking on the idea that in a world dominated by AI, the company that stores the data the most efficiently and lets you use it for free will ultimately win the cloud war.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/wasabi-technologies-secures-250m-for-cloud-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">Wasabi Technologies Secures $250M for Cloud Expansion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
